Install Git on Linux
1.From your shell, install Git using apt-get:
$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install git
2.Verify the installation was successful by typing 
git --version:
$ git --version
 git version 2.9.2


create folder tarminal:mkdir folder name

............................................................
3.Configure your Git username and email using the following commands, replacing Emma's name with your own. These details will be associated with any commits that you create:

$ git config --global user.name "codersharif"
 $ git config --global user.email "khansharifulislam24@gmail.com"

:::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
…or create a new repository on the command line
echo "# gittest" >> README.md
git init            // git init kon project e ekbar use korle ar use korte hobe na.
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git remote add origin https://github.com/codersharif/gittest.git    //file age theke github e add thakle eta ar use kora lagbe na 
git push -u origin master


::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::::
…or push an existing repository from the command line
$ git remote add origin https://github.com/codersharif/gittest.git
$ git push -u origin master

$ git pull origin master   //eta use kori tokhon  ,, jodi amra github e kon text edit kori ,seta jodi computer e ante cai tahole use korte hobe.

$ git clone project souece link exmple:https://github.com/codersharif/ubundu17.10.git   ....jokhon ami anno folder e kaj korte cai ...tokhon gitgub tekhe ante hole eta use korte hobe.
 exm:$ git clone https://github.com/codersharif/ubundu17.10.git


$ git status 
$git show

